sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects a command line process that uses explorer.exe to launch arbitrary commands or binaries,
which is similar to cmd.exe /c, only it breaks the process tree and makes its parent a new instance of explorer spawning from "svchost"
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems), @gott_cyber

attributes.magic: DOS batch file, ASCII text, with CRLF line terminators

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The batch script first opens a URL, `https://www.healthfirst.com/privacy/`, in the default web browser using `explorer.exe`.  Then, it executes a program located at `%HOMEPATH%\datax\data\fontdiag.exe` in the background using `START /B`.  This program is run with the arguments `-drive file=%HOMEPATH%\datax\data\tc.img -nographic`. Finally, the script exits.  The script downloads no files itself; however,  `fontdiag.exe` may download files based on its internal logic and the provided `tc.img` file. The script relies on pre-existing files located in the `%HOMEPATH%\datax\data` directory.
